<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="42">Distinguished from all other cynolebiatins by two unambiguous synapomorphies (Costa, 2006a): a long (vs. short) hyomandibula and a narrowed (vs. wide) proximal tip of the fourth ceratobranchial.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
